      "abstract": "The PCL-5 is a 20-item self-report measure assessing symptoms of post-traumatic stress disorder based on DSM-5 criteria. Items are rated on a 5-point scale (0=Not at all, 4=Extremely). The PCL-5 can be used as a screening tool, diagnostic aid, and severity measurement for PTSD.",
